Once you can sit again,

709
01:05:59,924 --> 01:06:01,375
which could be a while, I admit.

710
01:06:01,410 --> 01:06:05,073
we’re going to my bank and tell them that
I alone have access to money.

711
01:06:05,108 --> 01:06:06,590
Nod.

712
01:06:06,625 --> 01:06:08,934
After that,
you’ll never contact me again.

713
01:06:09,533 --> 01:06:13,475
Each month you’ll prepare a report
of a meeting we will never have.

714
01:06:14,329 --> 01:06:16,435
In it, you’ll describe
how well I’m doing,

715
01:06:16,470 --> 01:06:18,106
how 'sociable' I’m becoming.

716
01:06:18,141 --> 01:06:20,679
Then, you will negotiate
with the court--

717
01:06:20,714 --> 01:06:23,222
to have my
declaration of incompetence lifted.

718
01:06:23,257 --> 01:06:24,569
If you fail,

719
01:06:24,570 --> 01:06:27,345
this video will spread
across the Internet like a virus.

720
01:06:27,380 --> 01:06:28,682
Nod.

721
01:06:30,139 --> 01:06:31,888
And, If something happens to me

722
01:06:31,923 --> 01:06:35,846
..if I get hit by a car -
if you run me over with a car -

723
01:06:35,881 --> 01:06:37,708
This will upload automatically.

724
01:06:37,743 --> 01:06:39,717
Nod that you understand.

725
01:06:43,233 --> 01:06:44,683
Oh, Gabardina.

726
01:06:45,705 --> 01:06:47,774
I’m taking the keys to this apartment.

727
01:06:47,809 --> 01:06:49,421
Because, I’ll  be checking on you.

728
01:06:49,456 --> 01:06:51,387
And If I find a girl in here with you,

729
01:06:51,422 --> 01:06:53,528
whether she came of her own
free will or not -

730
01:06:56,664 --> 01:06:58,075
No.  Not the video.

731
01:07:06,993 --> 01:07:08,294
I will kill you.

732
01:07:10,468 --> 01:07:12,195
Do you doubt anything I’ve said?

733
01:07:13,130 --> 01:07:16,699
Do you doubt in the
reports that've followed me all my life?

734
01:07:16,734 --> 01:07:18,035
What do they say?

735
01:07:18,616 --> 01:07:19,941
If you had to sum it up?

736
01:07:20,848 --> 01:07:22,394
They say I’m insane.

737
01:07:23,453 --> 01:07:26,120
No, it okay. You can nod
because it’s true.

738
01:07:27,578 --> 01:07:29,141
I am insane.

739
01:07:30,941 --> 01:07:32,242
Nod!

740
01:07:34,774 --> 01:07:37,181
I know it’ll be hard for you
to abide by my rules.

741
01:07:37,986 --> 01:07:40,117
The abstinence part,
most of all.

742
01:07:42,463 --> 01:07:44,183
So, I’m going to make it
easier for you.

743
01:07:56,912 --> 01:07:59,656
Lie still.  I’ve never
done this before.

744
01:08:00,272 --> 01:08:02,085
And, There will be some blood.

745
01:09:27,666 --> 01:09:29,269
- Hi.
- Hi.

746
01:09:30,219 --> 01:09:32,421
- What are you doing here?
- On my way to Skelleftea.

747
01:09:32,422 --> 01:09:34,008
I can only
stay for four hours.

748
01:09:36,860 --> 01:09:38,162
What’s in Skelleftea?

749
01:09:39,690 --> 01:09:41,030
Bible Camp.

750
01:09:43,191 --> 01:09:44,174
Oh, yeah.

751
01:10:04,538 --> 01:10:06,844
- I'm not dangerous.
- It’s fine, Nilla.

752
01:10:07,874 --> 01:10:09,840
Whatever you want to do is fine.

753
01:10:09,875 --> 01:10:13,282
-  Everybody needssomething.
- Just so long as it’s not God.

754
01:10:13,318 --> 01:10:14,731
I didn’t say that.

755
01:10:19,123 --> 01:10:22,379
I’ve never been around enough to know
everything that’s going on with you,

756
01:10:24,804 --> 01:10:26,496
and I apologize for that.

757
01:10:27,676 --> 01:10:29,276
But I’d never want
you to not tell me something,

758
01:10:29,311 --> 01:10:31,516
B'cos you think
I might not want to hear it.

759
01:10:32,638 --> 01:10:33,977
That’s what I’m doing.

760
01:10:35,936 --> 01:10:38,152
It really should have been me visiting you.
I’m sorry.

761
01:10:38,188 --> 01:10:40,879
It’s okay.
It was nice seeing you.

762
01:10:42,085 --> 01:10:43,387
Bye bye.

763
01:10:43,743 --> 01:10:45,180
- See you.
- Yeah.

764
01:10:49,753 --> 01:10:51,563
Don’t go too hard on the Catholics.

765
01:10:51,564 --> 01:10:52,892
What?

766
01:10:52,893 --> 01:10:54,469
The article you’re writing.

767
01:10:54,470 --> 01:10:56,245
I'm not writing an article
about Catholics.

768
01:10:56,246 --> 01:10:58,129
The Bible quotes on your desk...

769
01:11:38,374 --> 01:11:43,249
<i>A woman who is a medium
or a sorcerer; shall be put to death, by stoning.</i>

770
01:11:44,860 --> 01:11:46,957
<i>If a dove is the sinner’s offering, </i>

771
01:11:46,992 --> 01:11:49,092
<i>the priest shall wring off its head, </i>

772
01:11:49,127 --> 01:11:52,347
<i> cleave its wings, and burn it upon the altar.</i>

773
01:11:55,554 --> 01:11:56,855
Hello.

774
01:11:56,856 --> 01:11:58,569
Detective Morell,
it’s Mikael Blomkvist.

775
01:11:58,604 --> 01:12:00,212
Yes, Hello.
How are you?

776
01:12:00,247 --> 01:12:03,009
Not still freezing in Hedestad,
I hope for your sake.

777
01:12:03,044 --> 01:12:06,054
You know, The Rebecka Case
that you mentioned.

778
01:12:06,089 --> 01:12:07,872
Would you recall the last name?

779
01:12:07,907 --> 01:12:10,510
Of course I do, but what would it
have to do with anything?

780
01:12:10,545 --> 01:12:14,841
- Nothing probably.
- Jocobsson. Rebecka Jocobsson.

781
01:12:16,437 --> 01:12:17,964
How was she killed?

782
01:12:17,999 --> 01:12:22,515
She was decapitated.
Her arms were cut off and she was burned.

783
01:12:22,550 --> 01:12:25,479
But all this happened in the 1940’s -

784
01:12:27,282 --> 01:12:28,583
What have you found?

785
01:12:28,618 --> 01:12:31,437
- I’m gonna have to call you back.
- Why?

786
01:12:44,034 --> 01:12:45,713
- Is it Henrik?
- We were talking.

787
01:12:45,748 --> 01:12:47,744
He started rubbing at his arm
an then collapsed.

788
01:12:47,745 --> 01:12:49,046
Is he gonna be okay?

789
01:12:49,047 --> 01:12:50,832
I can’t talk, Mikael,
I honestly don't know -

790
01:12:50,833 --> 01:12:52,134
- You gotta go.
- I'm sorry.

791
01:12:52,135 --> 01:12:53,580
I'll talk to you later.

792
01:13:04,644 --> 01:13:05,945
Good evening.

793
01:13:07,989 --> 01:13:09,625
Come on up,
How is he?

794
01:13:10,136 --> 01:13:13,069
Well, The good news is he survived.

795
01:13:13,104 --> 01:13:14,766
How  he does now,
we have to see.

796
01:13:15,342 --> 01:13:17,399
-  He’s in Intensive Care.
- Right.

797
01:13:20,394 --> 01:13:22,045
-  Can I have one of those?
- You want a sandwich?

798
01:13:22,748 --> 01:13:24,955
- A small Scotch.
- Sure thing.

799
01:13:29,705 --> 01:13:31,006
Thank you.

800
01:13:31,041 --> 01:13:33,488
I hate to be indelicate. But...

801
01:13:33,523 --> 01:13:36,569
Henrik promised me something
when I agreed to do this.

802
01:13:36,604 --> 01:13:39,111
- Yeah, Wennerström.
- I need to know what he has on him.

803
01:13:39,730 --> 01:13:42,462
- Now.  In case.
- In case he dies?

804
01:13:43,090 --> 01:13:45,602
-  That is indelicate.
- And I apologize.

805
01:13:45,638 --> 01:13:48,450
Well, I don’t know what he has on him,
if you’re asking me.

806
01:13:48,485 --> 01:13:51,118
And he can’t tell you
in the condition he’s in.

807
01:13:53,517 --> 01:13:55,975
We also didn't discussed
who I’d report

808
01:13:56,011 --> 01:13:59,739
- to if something happened to him.
- Who else, You'd report to me.

809
01:14:00,306 --> 01:14:03,128
We both know nothing’s going
to come of this, don't we?

810
01:14:04,379 --> 01:14:06,890
No, we don't know that.

811
01:14:06,925 --> 01:14:08,226
What do you mean?

812
01:14:09,088 --> 01:14:11,378
- I may have found something.
- You're joking?

813
01:14:12,221 --> 01:14:13,522
What have you found?

814
01:14:14,470 --> 01:14:17,859
The last time I reported on something
without being absolutely sure,

815
01:14:17,894 --> 01:14:19,658
I lost me my life savings.

816
01:14:20,296 --> 01:14:22,965
I need a research assistant.
Can you authorize that?

817
01:14:22,966 --> 01:14:24,283
Yes.

818
01:14:24,284 --> 01:14:27,235
- Do you have one in mind?
- I can find someone.

819
01:14:27,270 --> 01:14:30,528
I know a excellent one.  She did the
background check on you.

820
01:14:30,563 --> 01:14:32,000
The what?

821
01:14:32,035 --> 01:14:36,178
You don't think we can hire just anyone
without doing background check?

822
01:14:37,407 --> 01:14:39,034
I want to read it.

823
01:14:39,456 --> 01:14:42,093
Herr Frode was kind enough to share
your report with me.

824
01:14:42,128 --> 01:14:44,979
The investigator’s name...
That is her name, yes?

825
01:14:46,148 --> 01:14:49,974
I can find no record of her, and
I’m pretty good at that kind of thing.

826
01:14:50,579 --> 01:14:52,239
Would it really matter?

827
01:14:52,274 --> 01:14:53,816
But It would if I wanted
to speak to her, Yes.

828
01:14:53,817 --> 01:14:55,147
It's against policy.

829
01:14:55,182 --> 01:14:57,858
- You sure?
- Just like your sources. You understand.

830
01:14:57,893 --> 01:14:59,195
Okay.

831
01:15:00,280 --> 01:15:01,853
Here's a name for you.

832
01:15:02,825 --> 01:15:05,359
My sister,
she's also my lawyer.

833
01:15:05,395 --> 01:15:07,242
She'll be contacting you.

834
01:15:07,277 --> 01:15:10,087
There’s information in here that
could only have come from one place.

835
01:15:14,384 --> 01:15:16,817
The reason you can find no record
of her is because

836
01:15:16,852 --> 01:15:18,561
her records have been sealed.

837
01:15:18,596 --> 01:15:20,984
-  She’s a ward of the State.
- What does that have to do with anything?

838
01:15:23,029 --> 01:15:24,837
She’s had a rough life.

839
01:15:25,635 --> 01:15:28,804
Can we please,
not make it rougher on her?

840
01:16:40,045 --> 01:16:41,346
Who is it?

841
01:16:41,919 --> 01:16:43,220
Mikael Blomkvist.

842
01:16:47,972 --> 01:16:51,116
- Actually I’m not really up (yet) -
- May I come in? Please.

843
01:16:58,259 --> 01:16:59,561
Hi.

844
01:16:59,562 --> 01:17:01,658
You and I need to talk.
I got us some break...

845
01:17:02,477 --> 01:17:04,254
I'm sorry, I need...

846
01:17:04,884 --> 01:17:06,185
Who do you think you are?

847
01:17:07,116 --> 01:17:09,984
I’m the guy you know
better than my closest friends do.

848
01:17:12,055 --> 01:17:14,794
Why don't you put some
clothes  on and get rid of your girlfriend.

849
01:17:15,664 --> 01:17:17,150
We need to talk.

850
01:17:26,864 --> 01:17:29,077
I'm sorry,
You have to go.

851
01:17:29,112 --> 01:17:30,588
Okay.

852
01:17:45,835 --> 01:17:47,214
Do you need me to stay?

853
01:17:48,996 --> 01:17:50,298
No.

854
01:17:56,588 --> 01:17:58,311
- Bye.
- Bye.

855
01:18:05,853 --> 01:18:07,154
Bye.

856
01:18:07,155 --> 01:18:08,767
- Sorry.
- Bye.

857
01:18:14,669 --> 01:18:17,160
I guess I alarmed you
turning up like that.

858
01:18:17,195 --> 01:18:19,298
If you touch me,
I’ll more than alarm you.

859
01:18:19,776 --> 01:18:21,272
That won’t be necessary.

860
01:18:22,413 --> 01:18:24,795
Your report, very detailed.

861
01:18:25,275 --> 01:18:26,932
but for me,
It wasn't very entertaining.

862
01:18:26,933 --> 01:18:29,268
- It wasn’t meant to be.
- When I write about people,

863
01:18:29,303 --> 01:18:31,342
I try to entertain the reader.

864
01:18:31,377 --> 01:18:33,292
Wennerström
wasn’t entertained much.

865
01:18:37,555 --> 01:18:40,258
Your boss, Armansky...

866
01:18:41,007 --> 01:18:44,563
He tells me, you only work on things
that interest you.

867
01:18:44,598 --> 01:18:46,413
So, I suppose..
I should be flattered.

868
01:18:47,870 --> 01:18:49,176
Are you going to sit down?

869
01:18:50,230 --> 01:18:55,506
He also says that
you’re the one he goes to

870
01:18:56,646 --> 01:18:58,902
When the jobs is, ‘sensitive’

871
01:18:58,937 --> 01:19:03,598
I'm gonna use,‘illegal,’ b'cos that's what it was
when you hacked into my computer.

872
01:19:03,634 --> 01:19:06,897
I’m not going to do anything about
that.  I could but I won’t.

873
01:19:06,932 --> 01:19:11,447
What I’m going to dois tell you a story.
If it entertains  you,

874
01:19:11,482 --> 01:19:13,660
maybe you’ll
decide to help me research further.

875
01:19:13,695 --> 01:19:16,978
And if not, then I'll do the washing
and you'll never see me again.

876
01:19:20,622 --> 01:19:22,603
What kind of research?

877
01:19:22,638 --> 01:19:24,974
Lisbeth...
Can I call you Lisbeth?

878
01:19:26,674 --> 01:19:29,243
I want you to help me
catch a killer of women.

879
01:19:30,645 --> 01:19:32,735
I've got "R. J.",
Rebecka Jacobsson.

880
01:19:32,770 --> 01:19:35,982
I have absolutely no idea
who the rest of this people are -

881
01:19:36,017 --> 01:19:38,648
or how they’re connected to the death
of a 16 year old girl -

882
01:19:38,683 --> 01:19:40,409
they must be somehow.

883
01:19:40,444 --> 01:19:43,624
So, what we're gonna do is find out who
they are? What happened to them?

884
01:19:43,659 --> 01:19:46,944
and what the Leviticus verses
have to do with anything?

885
01:19:49,791 --> 01:19:51,092
What are you doing?

886
01:19:51,093 --> 01:19:53,166
Getting started.  You can keep
talking if you want.

887
01:19:53,201 --> 01:19:56,752
- Don't you need to look over this?
- I got it.

888
01:20:42,874 --> 01:20:44,176
Cat!

889
01:21:14,298 --> 01:21:15,599
How did you get in?

890
01:21:25,503 --> 01:21:27,974
No one’s asked me about Magda
in over 40 years.

891
01:21:29,178 --> 01:21:32,232
Why would a young lady like you want
to know about such an aweful murder?

892
01:21:32,267 --> 01:21:34,884
- It interests me.
- Does it ?

893
01:21:38,265 --> 01:21:40,066
Her husband was our first suspect -

894
01:21:40,101 --> 01:21:43,397
the husband is always the first
suspect, and usually the last -

895
01:21:43,432 --> 01:21:44,802
but not this time.

896
01:21:44,837 --> 01:21:47,983
We moved on to a neighbor.
Then a vagrant -

897
01:21:49,033 --> 01:21:51,578
Once you get to strangers,
it’s only a matter of time...

898
01:21:51,613 --> 01:21:55,378
before you get to gypsies,
and you know you’re never going to solve it.

899
01:21:55,413 --> 01:21:56,980
How exactly was she killed?

900
01:21:58,704 --> 01:22:00,169
- Miss...
- Salander.

901
01:22:00,204 --> 01:22:02,464
I'm sorry..Miss Salander, I hope,
you don’t mind my asking,

902
01:22:02,465 --> 01:22:03,909
when’s the last time you ate?

903
01:22:03,910 --> 01:22:06,034
I have a high metabolism.
I can’t put on weight.

904
01:22:06,685 --> 01:22:10,346
I'm asking because it’s better to look at
what I’m about to show you

905
01:22:11,407 --> 01:22:12,987
on an empty stomach.

906
01:22:16,335 --> 01:22:20,893
<i>If a man’s offering is a lamb, it
shall be a female without blemish.</i>

907
01:22:20,928 --> 01:22:23,930
<i>He shall lay his hand upon it’s head
...slaughter it... </i>

908
01:22:23,965 --> 01:22:26,707
<i>empty it’s blood
on the base of the altar... </i>

909
01:22:26,742 --> 01:22:28,806
<i>and he shall be forgiven.</i>

910
01:22:33,302 --> 01:22:35,351
- How is he?
- He needs surgery

911
01:22:35,386 --> 01:22:37,399
but there’s no DNR in place.

912
01:22:37,434 --> 01:22:40,799
So it’s up to the family to decide

913
01:22:40,834 --> 01:22:42,302
whether to resuscitate or not,

914
01:22:42,979 --> 01:22:44,925
and they’re not good at decisions.

915
01:22:45,897 --> 01:22:48,165
- How’d it go with Ms. Salander?
- She said yes.

916
01:22:48,200 --> 01:22:49,958
Do you think
I might be able to see him?

917
01:22:49,993 --> 01:22:51,762
He was asleep when I last looked,

918
01:22:51,797 --> 01:22:54,339
- but let me check.
- Thank you.

919
01:22:54,340 --> 01:22:55,657
Don't check.

920
01:22:55,658 --> 01:22:58,602
- Tell him to pack his things and leave.
- Mother, please.

921
01:22:59,034 --> 01:23:00,430
Don’t use that tone with me.

922
01:23:00,465 --> 01:23:03,015
Isabella, Mr. Blomkvist
works for Henrik.

923
01:23:03,050 --> 01:23:05,173
- We should put this to a vote.
- Don’t be an idiot, Birger.

924
01:23:05,208 --> 01:23:07,710
We all know what Henrik wants,
Can we please just do that?

925
01:23:07,745 --> 01:23:11,916
Henrik is in there fighting for his life in there.
This is the last thing he needs.

926
01:23:11,951 --> 01:23:15,101
Excuse me, Mrs. Vanger,
there's nosmoke in here.

927
01:23:17,466 --> 01:23:18,963
Go back to Stockholm.

928
01:23:18,998 --> 01:23:21,517
When we need a family chronicle

929
01:23:21,552 --> 01:23:25,516
written by a libelist,
we know who to call.

930
01:23:31,533 --> 01:23:32,863
Alright, thanks.

931
01:23:34,440 --> 01:23:35,741
This way, Miss.

932
01:23:40,501 --> 01:23:43,981
<i>If a woman approaches any beast
and dies with it.</i>

933
01:23:44,016 --> 01:23:46,490
<i>He shall kill the woman and the beast,</i>

934
01:23:46,525 --> 01:23:48,863
<i>Their blood shall be upon them.</i>

935
01:24:02,142 --> 01:24:05,419
My family is impossible.
It’s why the company is such a mess.

936
01:24:07,325 --> 01:24:09,341
I apologize for my mother’s behavior.

937
01:24:09,742 --> 01:24:11,043
I'm use to it.

938
01:24:11,044 --> 01:24:13,478
It has nothing to do with you.
It’s between her and Henrik ...

939
01:24:14,068 --> 01:24:16,135
She lost it when my father died.

940
01:24:16,170 --> 01:24:21,982
Her drinking..it got so bad
Henrik took me and my sister away from her,

941
01:24:22,934 --> 01:24:27,917
And left her excommunicated,
in our old house on the other side of the island

942
01:24:27,952 --> 01:24:29,701
She hasn't forgiven him.

943
01:24:31,782 --> 01:24:33,154
You, you must stay.

944
01:24:34,327 --> 01:24:37,339
You’re last chance that  Henrik has
at some kind of resolution.

