02:18:42,090 --> 02:18:46,011
And I was.
Until, you showed up.

1427
02:18:47,934 --> 02:18:49,464
You're safe now.

1428
02:18:51,964 --> 02:18:53,533
How did you got away?

1429
02:18:55,389 --> 02:18:57,192
Someone saved me too.

1430
02:19:10,254 --> 02:19:11,839
- How're you feeling?
- I'm fine.

1431
02:19:11,840 --> 02:19:13,141
Thank you, Anna.

1432
02:19:15,157 --> 02:19:17,315
I made you a promise.

1433
02:19:19,572 --> 02:19:22,210
Whether you found anything,
or not.

1434
02:19:26,420 --> 02:19:29,635
So, What do you have to tell me?

1435
02:20:00,042 --> 02:20:01,620
Hello, Henrik.

1436
02:20:21,432 --> 02:20:23,506
I don’t even remember Wennerstrom
working here, much less

1437
02:20:23,541 --> 02:20:25,354
- being fired.
- How could you?

1438
02:20:25,389 --> 02:20:26,878
It was a long time ago.

1439
02:20:26,913 --> 02:20:31,208
Which is kind of more to the point than
the money he embezzled to start...

1440
02:20:31,243 --> 02:20:33,606
If you're referring to
the statued of limitation...

1441
02:20:33,641 --> 02:20:36,589
I had no idea, this was what
Henrik was holding out. If I had,

1442
02:20:36,624 --> 02:20:40,654
I never would have let him bring you up here.
He wasn’t trying to deceive you.

1443
02:20:40,655 --> 02:20:41,655
Oh, Come on, he knows you can’t try
somebody after 35 years after the event.

1444
02:20:43,569 --> 02:20:45,452
I like Henrik,
but he knows that.

1445
02:20:45,487 --> 02:20:47,679
A man’s reputation used to mean
something -

1446
02:20:47,680 --> 02:20:48,981
he still believes that.

1447
02:20:48,982 --> 02:20:51,921
I’m sure he thought you could destroy
Wennerstrom with this in the court of public opinion.

1448
02:20:51,956 --> 02:20:56,525
The “court of public opinion,”
now celebrates people's bad behaviour.

1449
02:20:56,560 --> 02:20:59,567
He promised me
Wennerstrom’s carcass on a plate.

1450
02:20:59,602 --> 02:21:02,878
This isn’t even the plate.
I can’t do anything with this.

1451
02:21:02,913 --> 02:21:04,605
Of course...

1452
02:21:08,552 --> 02:21:09,967
What happened with Wennerström?

1453
02:21:10,785 --> 02:21:12,086
How did he get you?

1454
02:21:13,102 --> 02:21:14,404
I was stupid.

1455
02:21:15,442 --> 02:21:17,884
I got something, I got it from
an anonymous source..

1456
02:21:17,919 --> 02:21:20,099
Who I'm sure, was one of
Wennerström's lakies

1457
02:21:22,573 --> 02:21:25,701
Which
he easily proved in court.

1458
02:21:26,923 --> 02:21:29,151
You were emphatic that the way I
looked into your life was illegal

1459
02:21:29,186 --> 02:21:30,860
and immoral.

1460
02:21:30,895 --> 02:21:32,802
Would you feel the same
about Wennerström?

1461
02:21:32,837 --> 02:21:34,214
Go on.

1462
02:21:34,592 --> 02:21:37,089
I did some work on my own on him,
before you hired me.

1463
02:21:37,090 --> 02:21:38,637
I haven’t had a chance to look at it all -

1464
02:21:38,672 --> 02:21:42,024
B'cos you and Harriet-fucking-Vanger
have kept me busy ...

1465
02:21:44,024 --> 02:21:47,516
-  but I may have something.
- You may have something?

1466
02:21:49,027 --> 02:21:50,328
Maybe.

1467
02:21:50,486 --> 02:21:52,946
They launder money from arms and drug
sales, and

1468
02:21:52,981 --> 02:21:54,682
crime syndicates in Russia.

1469
02:21:54,717 --> 02:21:58,229
And that money - accounts for all
but 5-percent of his holdings -

1470
02:21:58,264 --> 02:22:00,610
the rest ends up in accounts in the
Cayman Islands.

1471
02:22:00,645 --> 02:22:02,075
How do you know this?

1472
02:22:02,078 --> 02:22:03,602
This time you don’t want to know.

1473
02:22:03,603 --> 02:22:04,951
This time I do want to know.

1474
02:22:06,511 --> 02:22:08,179
I have access to his computer,

1475
02:22:08,636 --> 02:22:10,583
and
his accountants’ and lawyers’.

1476
02:22:10,618 --> 02:22:11,940
And how do you have that?

1477
02:22:11,975 --> 02:22:13,807
I could have gotten it from a source
inside the company.

1478
02:22:13,842 --> 02:22:15,533
- But you didn’t.
- But that’s what you’ll say.

1479
02:22:15,568 --> 02:22:17,108
But what will you say to me?

1480
02:22:18,072 --> 02:22:19,704
That depends on
if you really want to know.

1481
02:22:19,739 --> 02:22:22,021
I do. Mikael,
Who gave you access?

1482
02:22:35,090 --> 02:22:37,379
<i>Financial Journalist Mikael Blomkvist -
who this time</i>

1483
02:22:37,414 --> 02:22:40,328
<i> last year was convicted of libel
in a Stockholm courtroom - </i>

1484
02:22:40,364 --> 02:22:43,611
<i>doesn’t seem to have learned
from his mistakes. </i>

1485
02:22:44,041 --> 02:22:45,621
<i> Or maybe he has -</i>

1486
02:22:46,043 --> 02:22:48,268
<i>In the current issue of Millennium
magazine, </i>

1487
02:22:48,303 --> 02:22:52,417
<i>he now charges the same
company that successfully sued him - </i>

1488
02:22:52,452 --> 02:22:53,753
Before the shit hits the fan.

1489
02:22:56,168 --> 02:22:57,469
What happens now?

1490
02:22:57,986 --> 02:23:00,518
He’ll say i'st a personal vendetta
but it won’t work.

1491
02:23:01,308 --> 02:23:03,372
The police will investigate,
FI will investigate.

1492
02:23:03,956 --> 02:23:06,543
Maybe we'll go to court.
Maybe he'll go to prison.

1493
02:23:07,428 --> 02:23:08,729
Do you think?

1494
02:23:09,036 --> 02:23:12,372
Probably, not.
This guys never do.

1495
02:23:25,056 --> 02:23:27,195
- What’s wrong?
- It’s embarrassing.

1496
02:23:27,230 --> 02:23:28,785
Tell me.

1497
02:23:28,820 --> 02:23:30,404
I need to borrow some money.

1498
02:23:31,251 --> 02:23:32,552
50,000.

1499
02:23:34,555 --> 02:23:37,447
I have a chance to make an investment.
It’s a smart, safe investment.

1500
02:23:38,489 --> 02:23:40,226
I really don't think I've got 50,000.

1501
02:23:40,261 --> 02:23:41,911
Yes, you do.

1502
02:23:41,946 --> 02:23:44,094
You have 65 thousand
in your two accounts.

1503
02:23:45,408 --> 02:23:46,900
I’m sorry that I know that.

1504
02:23:49,160 --> 02:23:50,928
You’ll get the money back.
I promise.

1505
02:23:52,337 --> 02:23:55,289
- Okay.
- Okay.

1506
02:23:56,800 --> 02:23:58,512
You want a coffee?

1507
02:24:02,128 --> 02:24:06,700
<i>These allegations - like the last
ones from this so-called journalist - </i>

1508
02:24:06,735 --> 02:24:08,918
<i>are as ridiculous as they are untrue -</i>

1509
02:24:08,953 --> 02:24:12,251
<i>I’ll be seeing Mr. Blomkvist in court again.
I’m looking forward to it.</i>

1510
02:24:12,286 --> 02:24:13,856
<i>What about his documentation?</i>

1511
02:24:13,891 --> 02:24:16,005
<i>Fabricated.  All of it.</i>

1512
02:24:16,040 --> 02:24:19,782
<i>The Securities Fraud Office isn’t
quite as certain as Mr. Wennerstrom of that.</i>

1513
02:24:19,817 --> 02:24:23,459
<i>If even a fraction of what Mr.
Blomkvist is alleging proves to be true,</i>

1514
02:24:23,494 --> 02:24:26,060
<i> not only will there be
a securities investigation,</i>

1515
02:24:26,095 --> 02:24:28,609
<i> but an organized crime
inquiry as well.</i>

1516
02:24:28,644 --> 02:24:30,231
<i>Mr. Blomkvist names no sources.</i>

1517
02:24:30,266 --> 02:24:31,893
<i>And we can’t force him to.
But we can look for them.</i>

1518
02:24:31,894 --> 02:24:33,820
<i>- Beginning where?
- Beginning with...</i>

1519
02:24:33,821 --> 02:24:36,123
<i> those closest to Mr. Wennerström,  </i>

1520
02:24:36,158 --> 02:24:39,777
<i>Only someone in the inner circle of a
corporation like this could have access</i>

1521
02:24:39,812 --> 02:24:41,348
<i> to this kind of information. </i>

1522
02:24:41,383 --> 02:24:45,050
<i>Mr. Wennerström isn’t available for 
comment today, </i>

1523
02:24:45,051 --> 02:24:46,583
<i>but I’d be happy to answer 
your questions.</i>

1524
02:24:46,584 --> 02:24:48,114
<i>- Where is he??
- No, he's not.</i>

1525
02:24:48,149 --> 02:24:50,026
<i>Has he left the country?</i>

1526
02:24:50,061 --> 02:24:52,203
<i>I don't think so.</i>

1527
02:25:03,339 --> 02:25:04,847
Thank you.

1528
02:25:45,486 --> 02:25:48,902
<i>With his failure to appear before a 
Security Exchange Commission panel, </i>

1529
02:25:48,937 --> 02:25:52,322
<i>a warrant has been issued for The 
Wennerström Group CEO.</i>

1530
02:25:52,357 --> 02:25:54,798
<i>I can confirm that he left Sweden on
a private jet </i>

1531
02:25:54,833 --> 02:25:57,383
<i>that landed in Paris last week, </i>

1532
02:25:58,652 --> 02:26:00,463
<i>but whether he’s still there, 
we don’t know.  </i>

1533
02:26:01,855 --> 02:26:03,673
<i>He could be anywhere by now.</i>

1534
02:26:14,800 --> 02:26:16,101
Thank you.

1535
02:26:17,989 --> 02:26:20,755
I have a number of accounts at Bank
of Kroenfeld, Cayman Islands.

1536
02:26:20,790 --> 02:26:23,527
  I'd like to transfer those accounts
 and convert them to bonds.

1537
02:26:23,562 --> 02:26:25,455
Naturally, 
you have the clearingcodes.

1538
02:26:25,490 --> 02:26:26,791
Naturally.

1539
02:26:28,001 --> 02:26:29,870
How many accounts
 will you be transferring?

1540
02:26:29,905 --> 02:26:31,231
Thirty.

1541
02:26:32,729 --> 02:26:34,031
This will take some time.

1542
02:26:34,066 --> 02:26:36,596
For which you’ll receive 
a 4-percent commission.

1543
02:26:36,631 --> 02:26:39,226
- I will?
- Then it won’t be a waste of it.

1544
02:26:42,132 --> 02:26:45,032
<i>A Swedish tourist vacationing here in
Barbados says</i>

1545
02:26:45,067 --> 02:26:48,263
<i> he knows where fugitive financier
Hans-Erik Wennerström is:  </i>

1546
02:26:48,298 --> 02:26:51,411
<i>Here in this Caribbean island’s 
capital, Bridgetown. </i>

1547
02:26:51,446 --> 02:26:55,802
<i> Police released this photograph, yesterday- 
and say they believe is the disgraced billionaire.</i>

1548
02:27:10,545 --> 02:27:13,470
How many of these would you like to 
convert for deposit?

1549
02:27:13,505 --> 02:27:15,157
All fifty.  
Into five accounts.

1550
02:27:30,014 --> 02:27:31,883
That looks correct.

1551
02:28:44,412 --> 02:28:47,564
<i>The man who is now being called 
 "Sweden’s Charles Ponzi ",</i>

1552
02:28:47,599 --> 02:28:49,850
<i>may not have 
a country to call home,</i>

1553
02:28:49,885 --> 02:28:52,057
<i> but does have 
enough money to buy one.</i>

1554
02:28:52,092 --> 02:28:54,526
<i>According to the International 
Banking Commission,</i>

1555
02:28:54,561 --> 02:28:58,865
<i>Wennerström, a week after the 
Millennium article appeared on news stands, </i>

1556
02:28:58,900 --> 02:29:03,027
<i>began emptying accounts 
at Bank of Kroenfeld in the Cayman Islands.  </i>

1557
02:29:03,062 --> 02:29:06,240
<i>That money, approximately 
two billionEuros, </i>

1558
02:29:06,275 --> 02:29:08,417
<i>was then spread over a number of
 accounts with the help of </i>

1559
02:29:08,452 --> 02:29:12,133
<i>this confederate,
 seen here in Zurich -</i>

1560
02:29:16,188 --> 02:29:17,489
- Hey.
- Hey.

1561
02:29:17,841 --> 02:29:19,143
The money I borrowed.

1562
02:29:19,178 --> 02:29:20,498
Already?

1563
02:29:22,458 --> 02:29:24,595
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1564
02:29:28,235 --> 02:29:29,826
I quit.

1565
02:29:31,427 --> 02:29:32,729
Was it a good investment?

1566
02:29:33,422 --> 02:29:34,813
It was okay.

1567
02:29:36,037 --> 02:29:37,382
What are you doing later?

1568
02:29:38,037 --> 02:29:40,029
I'm seeing my daughter.

1569
02:29:40,064 --> 02:29:41,365
Okay.

1570
02:29:42,995 --> 02:29:44,296
You look nice.

1571
02:29:46,568 --> 02:29:47,981
It's Christmas again ... 

1572
02:29:49,529 --> 02:29:50,837
I'll see you soon.

1573
02:30:16,248 --> 02:30:17,694
I miss our meetings.  

1574
02:30:19,522 --> 02:30:21,391
I’m sure you don’t.
  Why would you?  

1575
02:30:21,967 --> 02:30:23,649
I was always such a headache for you.

1576
02:30:24,916 --> 02:30:27,346
Never showing up with good news.  
Only problems.

1577
02:30:29,425 --> 02:30:31,898
I have some good news now. 
 I’ve made a friend.  

1578
02:30:33,528 --> 02:30:35,634
I mean one that you’d 
approve of. 

1579
02:30:39,829 --> 02:30:41,131
I’m happy.

1580
02:30:47,149 --> 02:30:49,656
<i>- shot three times in the head at 
close range</i>

1581
02:30:49,691 --> 02:30:52,559
<i> in what is being called a 
classic gangland execution.  </i>

1582
02:30:52,594 --> 02:30:56,400
<i>The investigation into Wennerstrom’s 
ties to crime organizations worldwide will</i>

1583
02:30:56,435 --> 02:30:58,281
<i>now turn to speculation:  </i>

1584
02:30:58,316 --> 02:31:01,822
<i>Which of them caught up with him before 
Swedish authorities could? </i>

1585
02:31:01,857 --> 02:31:04,581
<i>Wennerström spent 
the last days of..</i>

1586
02:31:16,662 --> 02:31:17,963
It’s perfect.

1587
02:31:17,964 --> 02:31:20,787
- Your father?
- A friend.

1588
02:31:20,822 --> 02:31:22,477
Must be a very good friend.